    <title>Your iPhone 16 may get its first Apple Intelligence features later this month</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Illustration of the Apple logo with a slice falling out of it, implying breaking up a monopoly." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Eos9NZhoPGl7PYs1ND1KQaV9hoo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73635244/STK468_APPLE_ANTITRUST_CVIRGINIA_B.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="s1jiWe"&gt;The iPhone 16, despite its marketing so far, still &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/10/24241043/apple-iphone-16-pro-intelligence-ai-missing"&gt;doesn’t have&lt;/a&gt; Apple Intelligence. That’s set to change on October 28th with the release of iOS 18.1, according to &lt;em&gt;Bloomberg&lt;/em&gt;’s Mark Gurman in &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/10/24237714/apple-intelligence-generative-ai-features-update-schedule"&gt;today’s &lt;em&gt;Power On &lt;/em&gt;newsletter&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="nb3WcZ"&gt;The update will bring with it AI-powered notification summaries, Gurman writes. Though he only lists that example, the iOS 18.1 beta &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249206/apple-intelligence-ios-18-1-public-beta"&gt;has also included&lt;/a&gt; some Siri improvements (like understanding you better when you &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24171936/apple-siri-ai-update-ios18-features-wwdc"&gt;stumble over your words&lt;/a&gt;), along with writing tools and a new rainbow-colored glowing edge graphic when you summon Siri on a phone or iPad.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"&gt;&lt;aside id="ucaO1s"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="readmore" data-anthem-component-data='{"stories":[{"title":"The iPhone 16 will ship as a work in progress","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/10/24241043/apple-iphone-16-pro-intelligence-ai-missing"},{"title":"iOS 18 is a smart upgrade, even without the AI","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/16/24245582/ios-18-review-customization-apple-intelligence-siri"},{"title":"Here’s what your iPhone 16 will do with Apple Intelligence — eventually","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/10/24237714/apple-intelligence-generative-ai-features-update-schedule"}]}'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/aside&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="PcuZan"&gt;Apple Intelligence only runs on the iPhone 15 Pro and up, but it’s also been &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249206/apple-intelligence-ios-18-1-public-beta"&gt;available in beta&lt;/a&gt; for Macs and iPads with Apple silicon chips (M1 and and up), so even if you...&lt;/p&gt;
